  "message": "fix(ui): improve mobile responsiveness across visualization components\n\nAdd responsive breakpoints and layout adjustments to ensure technical\narticle visualizations render properly on smaller screens:\n\n- bakery-visualizations: Add sm: breakpoint for hero and process nexus\n  container min-heights, reducing cramped layouts on mobile\n- barra-visualizations: Add flex-wrap to header controls, responsive\n  text sizing for capital impact display, hide non-essential labels on\n  small screens, improve button/tab scrolling behavior\n- cmaes-article: Add responsive padding to math container\n- cmaes-visualizations: Add responsive padding throughout, flex-wrap\n  header controls, responsive button sizing, smaller 3D canvas height\n  on mobile\n- hoeffding-visualizations: Add flex-wrap to stress test header, make\n  mode toggle buttons full-width on mobile\n- raptorq-article: Reduce comparison table min-width slightly for\n  better mobile fit\n\nThese changes ensure the interactive financial and mathematical\nvisualizations remain usable on phones and tablets without horizontal\nscrolling or clipped UI elements.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
